The paper deals with the concept of positive semidefinite rank, which has applications in combinatorial optimization and communication complexity. This suggests that the paper could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper uses techniques based on quantum communication protocols, which could place it in cs.QI (Quantum Physics) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper involves matrix factorization and optimization, which could relate to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
